# fixes #30 (2026-07-10, reverses the 2026-06-30 shared-config decision): a device paired under the
# OLD scheme (config.json in .userdata/shared/Lodor) must NOT be forced to re-onboard on this update.
# lodor_migrate_cfg moves the old shared config INTO the pak dir on the first pak open, non-destructively.
desc cfgmove #30: pre-#30 shared config is migrated into the pak dir on open, then removed from shared
oldconfig paired
seeded
pick 0|Sync now
pick 2|
engine 0|RESULT ok
expect_exit 0
# migrated INTO the pak dir, carrying the old token (no re-onboarding)
expect_file_has Tools/tg5040/Lodor.pak/config.json	OLD-SHARED-TOKEN
expect_file_has Tools/tg5040/Lodor.pak/settings.conf	mirror_mode=merge
expect_file_has Tools/tg5040/Lodor.pak/active-profile.txt	old-device
# and NON-DESTRUCTIVELY removed from the old shared home (no lingering credential)
expect_file_absent .userdata/shared/Lodor/config.json
expect_file_absent .userdata/shared/Lodor/settings.conf
expect_file_absent .userdata/shared/Lodor/active-profile.txt
